44 m_bool initialize_object(M_Object object, Type type)
45 {
46  if (!type->info) {
47  err_msg(TYPE_, 0, "internal error: no type->info for type '%s'", type->name);
48  return -1;
49  }
50  object->vtable = type->info->obj_v_table;
51  object->type_ref = type;
52  object->size = type->obj_size;
53  if (object->size) {
54  object->d.data = calloc(object->size, sizeof(unsigned char));
55  if (!object->d.data)
56  goto out_of_memory;
57  memset(object->d.data, 0, object->size);
58  } else
59  object->d.data = NULL;
60  return 1;
61 
62 out_of_memory:
63  err_msg(TYPE_, 0, "OutOfMemory: while instantiating object '%s'\n", type->name);
64  return -1;
65 }

67 void release(M_Object obj, VM_Shred shred)
68 {
69  if (!obj)
70  return;
71  if (!--obj->ref) {
72  Type t = obj->type_ref;
73  while (t) {
74 #ifdef DEBUG_INSTR
75  debug_msg("instr", "dtor loop %p %s", obj, t->name);
76 #endif
77  m_uint i;
78  Vector v = scope_get(t->info->value);
79  for(i = 0; i < vector_size(v); i++) {
80  Value value = (Value)vector_at(v, i);
81  if(isprim(value->m_type) < 0)
82  release(*(M_Object*)(obj->d.data + value->offset), shred);
83  }
84  free_Vector(v);
85  if (t->has_destructor) {
86  if (t->info->dtor->native_func)
87  ((f_dtor)t->info->dtor->native_func)(obj, shred);
88  else {
89  VM_Code code = new_VM_Code(t->info->dtor->instr, SZ_INT, 1, "[dtor]", "[in code dtor exec]");
90  VM_Shred sh = new_VM_Shred(code);
91  sh->me = new_Shred(shred->vm_ref, sh);
92  memcpy(sh->mem, shred->mem, SIZEOF_MEM);
93  vector_pop(code->instr);
94  Instr eoc = new_Instr();
95  eoc->execute = EOC;
96  vector_append(code->instr, (vtype)eoc);
97  vm_add_shred(shred->vm_ref, sh);
98  }
99  }
100  t = t->parent;
101  }
102  }
103 }

111 INSTR(Assign_Object)
112 {
113 #ifdef DEBUG_INSTR
114  debug_msg("instr", "assign object %p %p", instr->m_val, *(m_uint*)(shred->reg - SZ_INT * 2), **(m_uint**)(shred->reg - SZ_INT));
115 #endif
116  POP_REG(shred, SZ_INT * 2);
117  M_Object done = **(M_Object**)(shred->reg + SZ_INT);
118  if(done)
119  release(done, shred);
120  (**(m_uint**)(shred->reg + SZ_INT) = *(m_uint*)shred->reg);
121  PUSH_REG(shred, SZ_INT);
122 }

154 INSTR(Vararg_start)
155 {
156 #ifdef DEBUG_INSTR
157  debug_msg("instr", "vararg start %i", instr->m_val);
158 #endif
159  struct Vararg* arg = *(struct Vararg**)(shred->mem + instr->m_val);
160  if (!arg->d)
161  shred->next_pc = instr->m_val2 + 1;
162  PUSH_REG(shred, SZ_INT);
163  *(m_uint*)(shred->reg - SZ_INT) = 0;
164 }
165 
166 INSTR(Vararg_end)
167 {
168  struct Vararg* arg = *(struct Vararg**)(shred->mem + instr->m_val);
169  switch (arg->k[arg->i]) {
170  case Kindof_Int:
171  arg->o += SZ_INT;
172  break;
173  case Kindof_Float:
174  arg->o += SZ_FLOAT;
175  break;
176  case Kindof_Complex:
177  arg->o += SZ_COMPLEX;
178  break;
179  case Kindof_Vec3:
180  arg->o += SZ_VEC3;
181  break;
182  case Kindof_Vec4:
183  arg->o += SZ_VEC4;
184  break;
185  // can you reach this ?
186  case Kindof_Void:
187  case Kindof_Ptr:
188  break;
189  }
190  PUSH_REG(shred, SZ_INT);
191  arg->i++;
192  if (arg->i == arg->s) {
193  free(arg->d);
194  free(arg->k);
195  free(arg);
196  } else {
197  *(m_uint*)(shred->reg - SZ_INT) = 0;
198  shred->next_pc = instr->m_val2;
199  }
200 }

243 m_bool import_object(Env env)
244 {
245  CHECK_BB(add_global_type(env, &t_object))

248  CHECK_BB(add_binary_op(env, op_at_chuck, &t_null, &t_object, &t_object, Assign_Object, 1, 0))
